                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=andyfowler",
                        "name": "andyfowler",
                        "displayName": "Andy Fowler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'd vote for this to enter the 1.9.x cycle. I'm slightly confused on Matthew's stance, because he seems to be endorsing the new behavior in the last example on his article: http:\/\/weierophinney.net\/matthew\/archives\/227-Exposing-Service-APIs-via-Zend-Framework.html\r\n\r\n(Overriding a .ini config with array data).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=andyfowler",
                        "name": "andyfowler",
                        "displayName": "Andy Fowler",
